x 0;">The $13 billion of debt financing is a bit different though. Technica=
lly=C2=A0<em>Musk=C2=A0</em>is not on the hook for that financing; his=C2=
=A0<em>banks=C2=A0</em>are. If they don=E2=80=99t come up with the money th=
en Musk can get out of the deal by paying a $1 billion breakup fee, whereas=
 if they do come up with the $13 billion then, at least in theory (that is,=
 under the terms of=C2=A0the merger agreement), Twitter can go to court to =
get a judge to order Musk to pay the other $33.5 billion and buy Twitter.=
